<div class="about-content post">
    <h2 class="header">Registration Policy</h2>
    <div>
        <div class="sub">
            <p class="q">REGISTRATION POLICY</p>
            <div class="sub">
                <p class="q">A. AUTHOR REGISTRATION POLICY</p>
                <div class="sub">
                    <p>It is mandatory for the authors to register at the full conference rates</p>

                    <p>An additional paper by the same author needs no additional registration</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="sub">
                <p class="q">B. DELEGATE REGISTRATION POLICY</p>
                <div class="sub">
                    <p>It is mandatory for all the delegates to register at the full conference rates.</p>

                    <p>On spot registrations are open for delegates during the event. It is mandatory for such</p>

                    <p>registrants to pay 100% payment on the spot</p>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub">
            <p class="q">REFUND POLICY</p>

            <div class="sub">
                <p class="q">A. AUTHOR REFUND</p>
                <div class="sub">
                    <p>In any case author is not eligible for a refund after the paper is included in online or offline</p>

                    <p>proceedings of the conference.</p>

                    <p>However, if the author withdraws the paper prior to the proceedings, the author is eligible for</p>

                    <p>a 50% refund.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="sub">
                <p class="q">B. DELLEGATE REFUND</p>

                <div class="sub">
                    <p class="q">1. Full refund</p>

                    <p>All the delegates who cancel their registrations 60 days before the start of the</p>

                    <p>conference are eligible for a complete refund of the registration fee.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="sub">
                    <p class="q">2. 50% refund</p>

                    <p>All the delegates who cancel their registrations after 60 days and before 45 days of the</p>

                    <p>start of the conference are eligible for a refund of 50% of the registration fee.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="sub">
                    <p class="q">3. No refund</p>

                    <p>All the delegates who cancel their registrations after 30 days before the start of the</p>

                    <p>conference are not eligible for any refund of the registration fee.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub">
            <p class="q">REGISTRATION TRANSFER POLICY</p>

            <div class="sub">
                <p>A. Authors are not eligible for transfer policy. However a replacement from the same</p>

                <p>organization can attend the conference on behalf of the author after registering afresh for the</p>

                <p>conference.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="sub">
                <p>B. Delegates who are not able to attend the conference can transfer their conference fee to</p>

                <p>future conferences with Scientific Cognizance.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub">
            <p class="q">EVENT CANCELLATION POLICY</p>

            <div class="sub">
                <p><i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> In case of postponement or cancellation of the conference registered delegates and speakers</p>

                <p>are entitled for a full refund.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="sub">
                <p><i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> Scientific Cognizance policy does not provide any additional refund for claims on air tickets or</p>

                <p>accommodation.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sub">
            <p class="q">MODE OF REFUND PAYMENT</p>

            <div class="sub">
                <p><i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> In case of payments made through credit or debit cards, the refunds will be credited back into</p>

                <p>the same credit or debit card.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="sub">
                <p><i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> In all other cases, a bank transfer will be made to the payee nominated account.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>